explanation: Provide the macro/implementations and type/constant definitions that can alter control flow or determine which branches are reachable. OS_CHECK_PATHNAME: may contain early-return, longjmp, or assertions that make later code unreachable. OS_ObjectIdGetByName: its implementation/attributes determine whether the if(return_code == OS_SUCCESS) branch can be taken or if it always/never returns, or if it is noreturn. OS_FileSysStopVolume_Impl: its implementation/attributes (including noreturn/longjmp) can make subsequent OS_ObjectIdFinalizeDelete call unreachable. OS_ObjectIdFinalizeDelete: its semantics may alter return_code or perform control-transfer; need to know if it is noreturn. OS_SUCCESS and OS_ERR_NAME_NOT_FOUND: constant values used in branch conditions and final return — required to determine distinct code paths. OS_object_token_t: type definition (and any associated macros) in case its usage or initialization has side effects or macros that affect flow. OS_LOCK_MODE_EXCLUSIVE and LOCAL_OBJID_TYPE: macros/enum values passed to OS_ObjectIdGetByName that could affect its behavior. int32: typedef for return type (may reveal attributes or qualifiers affecting control flow analysis).
